@startuml
' @id(SEQ-MAP-STATUS)
' @ref(USE-MAP-FRESHNESS)
' @desc(SEQ-MAP-STATUS, "`mdd map-status` (mdd-cli Commands::MapStatus -> Project::map_status()) reports diagram drift. It reads .mdd/map/manifest.yml source_revision (the commit at which the whole-map was last accurate, recorded at cycle close). With no whole-map yet (greenfield) it returns Fresh{no_baseline}. Otherwise it calls the same trace engine: changed_symbols(source_revision) via git diff + syn, intersects the changed symbols with trace.yml source_links; if any tracked symbol changed it returns Stale with the (path, symbol, @id) drift list, else Fresh. Output is one line plus the drift list, exit code 0 fresh / non-zero stale, so a SessionStart hook (cycle 0014) can surface it.")
' Objective sequence for the freshness check (cycle 0013). Reuses the
' DOM-SYMBOL-SPAN engine that backs SEQ-TRACE-REVIEW — the only new
' input is the recorded source_revision baseline.
title mdd map-status freshness (objective)

actor "Developer / Agent" as Dev
participant "mdd map-status\n(Commands::MapStatus)" as Cli
participant "Project::map_status()" as Status
participant ".mdd/map/manifest.yml" as Manifest
participant "Trace engine\n(git + syn)" as Engine
participant "trace.yml\nsource_links" as Trace

Dev -> Cli : mdd map-status
Cli -> Status : run
Status -> Manifest : read source_revision
alt no whole-map yet
  Manifest --> Status : absent
  Status --> Cli : Fresh { no_baseline }
else baseline present
  Manifest --> Status : source_revision
  Status -> Engine : changed_symbols(source_revision)
  Engine --> Status : changed (path, symbol)*
  Status -> Trace : which changed symbols are tracked by a source_link?
  Trace --> Status : tracked drift set
  alt drift set empty
    Status --> Cli : Fresh
  else drift set non-empty
    Status --> Cli : Stale { (path, symbol, @id)* }
  end
end
Cli --> Dev : status line + drift list (exit 0 fresh / non-zero stale)
@enduml
